verses.roman:
tāṅ-sabāra saṅge raghunātha yāite nā pāre
prasiddha prakaṭa saṅga, tabahiṅ dharā paḍe

synonyms: tāṅ-sabāra—all of them; saṅge—with; raghunātha—Raghunātha dāsa; yāite nā pāre—could not go; prasiddha—famous; prakaṭa—known; saṅga—group; tabahiṅ—immediately; dharā paḍe—he would be caught.
translation: Raghunātha dāsa could not accompany them, for they were so famous that he would immediately have been caught.
